This paper discusses a new variant of the h index in research evaluation, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of computer science and interdisciplinary fields. The use of Stata and R for simulation also suggests a focus on data analysis and computational methods. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with information retrieval, data mining, and bibliometrics. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which all involve computational modeling and simulation.
